having sex while on the book tour together.</i>

479
00:27:37.422 --> 00:27:39.914
<i>I'm asking if you remember
something like that happening</i>

480
00:27:39.992 --> 00:27:41.790
<i>between you and
her during that time.</i>

481
00:27:43.595 --> 00:27:46.997
- No. Absolutely not.
<i>- Are you sure?</i>

482
00:27:47.466 --> 00:27:51.096
- This is fucking shit! What? No!
<i>- So that's not your memory?</i>

483
00:27:51.436 --> 00:27:54.065
- No!
<i>- Okay. That's it. then.</i>

484
00:27:54.139 --> 00:27:56.699
<i>I just needed a comment.
Thanks for your time.</i>

485
00:28:01.313 --> 00:28:02.313
What...

486
00:28:05.584 --> 00:28:06.847
Oh. fuck.

487
00:29:38.477 --> 00:29:39.477
Yes?

488
00:29:40.779 --> 00:29:43.613
Hi. I'm looking
for Benjamin Cruz.

489
00:29:49.821 --> 00:29:52.848
I'm Ben Cruz. Can I help you?

490
00:29:54.926 --> 00:29:59.057
I just wanted to ask
about your clinic. I...

491
00:30:01.500 --> 00:30:02.559
I need help.

492
00:30:03.468 --> 00:30:04.993
I think I have PTSD.

493
00:30:06.471 --> 00:30:07.471
Ah.

494
00:30:09.274 --> 00:30:10.274
What's your name?

495
00:30:11.777 --> 00:30:12.777
Gabrielle.

496
00:30:16.315 --> 00:30:17.476
Very nice to meet you.

497
00:30:18.884 --> 00:30:19.908
Come on inside.

498
00:30:27.292 --> 00:30:30.160
Danny. Isla. meet Gabrielle.

499
00:30:30.228 --> 00:30:32.026
She's here to learn
about our community.

500
00:30:32.364 --> 00:30:33.593
- Hey there.
- Hey.

501
00:30:35.434 --> 00:30:36.434
Hi.

502
00:30:38.103 --> 00:30:40.629
I thought I was the only one
who read real books anymore.

503
00:30:46.044 --> 00:30:47.404
How about I give you a tour?

504
00:30:53.151 --> 00:30:55.347
I believe in the healing power

505
00:30:55.821 --> 00:30:58.552
of the fresh air
and tilling the land.

506
00:30:59.224 --> 00:31:02.023
Everything here has been
designed to be self-sustaining.

507
00:31:02.394 --> 00:31:05.421
My patients get free lodging

508
00:31:05.564 --> 00:31:08.124
in return for their
time in the garden.

509
00:31:09.634 --> 00:31:11.694
So. are you a
veteran. Gabrielle?

510
00:31:12.637 --> 00:31:15.197
Um. no. I'm not.

511
00:31:16.308 --> 00:31:17.640
How did you find us. then?

512
00:31:18.677 --> 00:31:19.872
Recommendation.

513
00:31:22.714 --> 00:31:26.310
I only ask because we
mostly service ex-military.

514
00:31:26.885 --> 00:31:31.255
When I was a young vet. I started
my post-service career at the VA

515
00:31:31.656 --> 00:31:35.320
during what I thought was a really
exciting time for PTSD therapy.

516
00:31:35.727 --> 00:31:38.629
Newer. integrative
psychotherapeutic approaches

517
00:31:38.697 --> 00:31:41.724
like exposure therapy. EMDR.

518
00:31:42.067 --> 00:31:45.902
They all seemed to be taking
root in the mainstream community.

519
00:31:46.671 --> 00:31:49.664
But then. of course.
they were obliterated

520
00:31:50.308 --> 00:31:54.404
as soon as the government
deregulated psychopharmaceutical drugs.

521
00:31:54.880 --> 00:31:58.840
If vets want alternative therapies.
they have to seek them under the table.

522
00:31:59.284 --> 00:32:02.721
pay out of pocket. get
treatments in secret.

523
00:32:02.888 --> 00:32:05.858
If the VA finds out. people
lose their health care.

524
00:32:07.659 --> 00:32:08.683
Anyway.

525
00:32:09.394 --> 00:32:12.626
that's why I have
to be extra careful

526
00:32:13.598 --> 00:32:15.260
when people knock on my door.

527
00:32:15.667 --> 00:32:19.331
Well. you weren't that careful.
You kind of just let me in.

528
00:32:21.573 --> 00:32:22.573
True.

529
00:32:24.543 --> 00:32:26.307
But you have an honest face.

530
00:32:29.648 --> 00:32:31.549
We grow all our own food.

531
00:32:31.616 --> 00:32:35.678
There's something so satisfying
about putting your hands in the dirt.

532
00:32:35.954 --> 00:32:39.118
turning the soil.
caring for the space.

533
00:32:39.357 --> 00:32:42.953
and then watch
it as it bears fruit.

534
00:32:44.629 --> 00:32:48.589
Here. the land that
we've taken care of

535
00:32:48.900 --> 00:32:50.869
then turns around
and cares for us.

536
00:32:51.436 --> 00:32:52.802
I firmly believe

537
00:32:53.738 --> 00:32:56.173
if we can remember
how to care for a garden.

538
00:32:59.144 --> 00:33:01.113
we can remember how
to care for each other.

539
00:33:11.022 --> 00:33:12.081
Thank you.

540
00:33:15.560 --> 00:33:17.085
Let's head back inside.

541
00:33:18.096 --> 00:33:19.860
Get to know each
other a bit better.

542
00:33:25.604 --> 00:33:28.233
So. Gabrielle.

543
00:33:29.374 --> 00:33:32.242
- That's a beautiful name. by the way.
- Thank you.

544
00:33:33.144 --> 00:33:34.510
Is it a family name?

545
00:33:36.248 --> 00:33:37.248
Yes.

546
00:33:40.418 --> 00:33:41.418
So tell me.

547
00:33:42.153 --> 00:33:43.314
how can I help you?

548
00:33:48.493 --> 00:33:50.553
I think I suffer from PTSD.

549
00:33:50.929 --> 00:33:53.831
Okay. How does that manifest?

550
00:33:56.501 --> 00:33:59.869
I can't connect with people.
I think I'm incapable of love.

551
00:34:01.206 --> 00:34:03.505
Well. sometimes such
feelings are connected

552
00:34:03.575 --> 00:34:07.273
to a significant loss or trauma

553
00:34:08.280 --> 00:34:09.612
at an early age.

554
00:34:11.683 --> 00:34:13.982
Does that resonate with you?

555
00:34:15.320 --> 00:34:16.320
No.

556
00:34:17.255 --> 00:34:18.255
Hmm.

557
00:34:19.457 --> 00:34:21.790
Are you familiar with EMDR?

558
00:34:22.661 --> 00:34:23.661
No.

559
00:34:24.195 --> 00:34:26.130
It's an old form of therapy.

560
00:34:27.165 --> 00:34:28.292
Nobody really understands

561
00:34:28.366 --> 00:34:32.269
why it works or
how. but it does.

562
00:34:32.504 --> 00:34:34.837
There's something
almost magical about it.

563
00:34:34.906 --> 00:34:38.104
Mm. You don't believe in magic?

564
00:34:38.510 --> 00:34:39.510
No.

565
00:34:41.313 --> 00:34:43.179
Maybe that's why
you have such...

566
00:34:44.649 --> 00:34:45.912
trouble with love.

567
00:34:48.954 --> 00:34:52.152
Would you like to try EMDR?

568
00:34:52.223 --> 00:34:55.193
Just to see if we
can get a little closer

569
00:34:55.260 --> 00:34:58.992
to understanding why you came.

570
00:35:02.934 --> 00:35:05.597
Sure. Why not?

571
00:35:06.137 --> 00:35:07.137
Excellent.

572
00:35:07.839 --> 00:35:11.241
I record all my
sessions. Do you mind?

573
00:35:13.044 --> 00:35:17.641
And this is just our
standard release form.

574
00:35:21.686 --> 00:35:24.417
- It's on paper.
- I know. What can I say?

575
00:35:24.856 --> 00:35:27.257
I am nostalgic for
the analog world.

576
00:35:28.126 --> 00:35:30.186
I suspect you are. too.

577
00:35:31.863 --> 00:35:34.423
Well. take a moment.
read it through.

578
00:35:34.799 --> 00:35:36.079
What's the date?

579
00:35:36.534 --> 00:35:39.129
Oh. don't worry about that.
I just need your signature.

580
00:35:41.506 --> 00:35:44.908
Okay. Thank you.

581
00:35:46.111 --> 00:35:47.111
So...

582
00:35:47.712 --> 00:35:50.181
the way EMDR works...

583
00:35:51.616 --> 00:35:55.417
we pick one specific
traumatic event

584
00:35:55.987 --> 00:35:57.956
and then we basically
rewrite the script

585
00:35:58.456 --> 00:36:01.654
so it doesn't trigger the
same debilitating response.

586
00:36:01.893 --> 00:36:03.828
Does that make sense? Good.

587
00:36:04.663 --> 00:36:07.656
We can start on
any memory. really.

588
00:36:08.800 --> 00:36:11.668
Is there a moment. a...

589
00:36:12.604 --> 00:36:15.096
a night where you remember this.

590
00:36:15.173 --> 00:36:18.166
as you say. "inability to love"

591
00:36:18.343 --> 00:36:20.278
really manifesting itself.

592
00:36:21.346 --> 00:36:23.338
impeding your life in some way?

593
00:36:26.251 --> 00:36:27.251
I...

594
00:36:30.088 --> 00:36:33.183
I had a fight with my
boyfriend recently.

595
00:36:34.492 --> 00:36:35.492
Excellent.

596
00:36:35.894 --> 00:36:38.955
That is the perfect thing
to unpack with this therapy.

597
00:36:40.365 --> 00:36:41.365
Let's start there.

598
00:36:42.133 --> 00:36:45.467
Can you please.
um. move your chair

599
00:36:46.604 --> 00:36:47.663
to face me?

600
00:36:50.809 --> 00:36:51.809
Good.

601
00:36:55.780 --> 00:36:59.273
No. see. you need
to be a little closer.

602
00:37:00.485 --> 00:37:02.078
There you go.

603
00:37:03.054 --> 00:37:07.924
Okay. to begin. just follow
my fingers with your eyes.

604
00:37:12.330 --> 00:37:14.458
- That makes me dizzy.
- Okay.

605
00:37:15.400 --> 00:37:18.768
Let's switch to something else.

606
00:37:20.405 --> 00:37:22.033
Your palms up.

607
00:37:22.907 --> 00:37:23.907
There you go.

608
00:37:27.812 --> 00:37:32.147
Close your eyes and
take a deep breath.

609
00:37:36.588 --> 00:37:38.921
Now think back to
the night of the fight.

610
00:37:40.425 --> 00:37:41.552
What do you notice?

611
00:37:42.827 --> 00:37:43.827
Where are you?

612
00:37:46.598 --> 00:37:47.896
I'm in my apartment.

613
00:37:48.299 --> 00:37:51.201
- Where is that?
- Montauk.

614
00:37:52.971 --> 00:37:54.491
How about your
boyfriend. is he there?

615
00:37:55.473 --> 00:37:56.668
He's on his way.

616
00:37:57.909 --> 00:38:01.346
- How do you feel?
- Scared.

617
00:38:01.713 --> 00:38:03.944
Good. Go with that.

618
00:38:06.384 --> 00:38:07.784
Same as before.

619
00:38:09.087 --> 00:38:12.421
Tell me... what do you notice?

620
00:38:14.058 --> 00:38:17.756
My apartment is warm. cozy.

621
00:38:17.829 --> 00:38:20.298
There's a fire in the fireplace.

622
00:38:21.533 --> 00:38:25.300
My daughter's drawings
are on the refrigerator.

623
00:38:26.771 --> 00:38:28.797
It's raining outside.

624
00:38:29.707 --> 00:38:34.008
Pouring. actually.
There's a storm. a bad one.

625
00:38:34.479 --> 00:38:35.708
The windows are rattling.

626
00:38:36.314 --> 00:38:37.748
Good. Go with that.

627
00:38:38.249 --> 00:38:41.014
Now what do you see happening?

628
00:38:41.686 --> 00:38:43.279
My boyfriend arrives.

629
00:38:43.855 --> 00:38:46.415
He's soaking wet. He
dries himself by the fire.

630
00:38:46.791 --> 00:38:47.850
How's he dressed?

631
00:38:48.660 --> 00:38:50.595
Jeans and a military jacket.

632
00:38:51.529 --> 00:38:52.656
He's a veteran.

633
00:38:54.499 --> 00:38:55.499
Good.

634
00:38:56.234 --> 00:38:57.463
Close your eyes.

635
00:38:59.370 --> 00:39:03.398
Notice what he
says and go with that.

636
00:39:04.008 --> 00:39:06.534
- He's angry.
- Why is he angry?

637
00:39:06.744 --> 00:39:08.110
Because he's married.

638
00:39:09.848 --> 00:39:11.908
and I want him
to leave his wife.

639
00:39:14.085 --> 00:39:14.916
We have a fight.

640
00:39:14.986 --> 00:39:17.854
I tell him that if he doesn't
leave her. I will kill myself.

641
00:39:18.556 --> 00:39:19.556
Keep going.

642
00:39:19.757 --> 00:39:23.524
He tells me that I'm ugly and stupid
and that nobody will ever love me.

643
00:39:23.595 --> 00:39:26.497
and that the best I could
hope for is to be someone's slut.

644
00:39:26.564 --> 00:39:28.692
Okay. That's enough.

645
00:39:30.602 --> 00:39:33.094
EMDR doesn't
work if you're lying.

646
00:39:46.551 --> 00:39:48.144
I never said those things.

647
00:39:49.454 --> 00:39:51.389
I respected your mother greatly.

648
00:39:53.625 --> 00:39:55.594
I would never have
spoken that way to her.

649
00:40:09.908 --> 00:40:11.001
Hello. Joanie.

650
00:40:12.043 --> 00:40:13.170
Hello. Ben.

651
00:40:15.146 --> 00:40:18.412
I'm so glad you
are finally here.

652
00:40:22.654 --> 00:40:24.987
Why don't we start again
with the same question?

653
00:40:26.391 --> 00:40:27.689
How can I help you?

654
00:40:32.730 --> 00:40:34.028
Did you kill my mother?

655
00:40:40.104 --> 00:40:41.104
Yes.

656
00:40:42.206 --> 00:40:43.206
I did.

657
00:40:51.482 --> 00:40:54.850
I can only imagine what
you think of me right now.

658
00:40:55.720 --> 00:40:57.621
It's all so new for you.

659
00:40:59.157 --> 00:41:02.821
The truth is. I've been
thinking about you for years.

660
00:41:03.561 --> 00:41:05.223
I've tried to imagine

661
00:41:05.596 --> 00:41:08.794
where you've been
living your life and how.

662
00:41:09.133 --> 00:41:13.400
I've awaited our reunion
with great anticipation.

663
00:41:17.642 --> 00:41:21.272
Is there anything else
you want to ask me?

664
00:41:21.980 --> 00:41:22.980
Anything at all?

665
00:41:24.782 --> 00:41:26.114
Go back behind your desk.

666
00:41:27.018 --> 00:41:28.680
I need a barrier between us.

667
00:41:29.854 --> 00:41:30.854
Of course.

668
00:41:38.563 --> 00:41:40.589
I want to be held
accountable. Joanie.

669
00:41:41.466 --> 00:41:44.459
I've always known I would eventually
have to answer for what I did.

670
00:41:45.803 --> 00:41:49.069
I welcome the opportunity.

671
00:41:53.845 --> 00:41:56.644
I know this might be
hard for you to believe.

672
00:41:57.181 --> 00:42:01.516
but I think of your
mother every day.

673
00:42:02.220 --> 00:42:04.416
Every minute. in fact.

674
00:42:05.623 --> 00:42:07.683
She is constantly with me.

675
00:42:09.127 --> 00:42:10.127
Eh...

676
00:42:11.596 --> 00:42:14.589
I hate myself for what I did.

677
00:42:15.033 --> 00:42:16.865
Okay. so. why did you do it?

678
00:42:19.470 --> 00:42:21.029
I had a psychotic break.

679
00:42:21.205 --> 00:42:23.936
- What?
- When I met your mother...

680
00:42:24.842 --> 00:42:27.710
the doctors at the VA
had me on a lot of drugs...

681
00:42:27.779 --> 00:42:31.978
Antidepressants.
MDMA. antipsychotics.

682
00:42:32.617 --> 00:42:34.085
I was losing my mind.

683
00:42:35.286 --> 00:42:38.916
I couldn't sleep.
I-I was paranoid.

684
00:42:38.990 --> 00:42:40.754
I started hearing voices.

685
00:42:40.825 --> 00:42:42.760
I didn't tell anyone.
of course. because...

686
00:42:42.827 --> 00:42:46.320
I was afraid they'd
lock me up for good.

687
00:42:47.832 --> 00:42:48.832
That night...

688
00:42:49.667 --> 00:42:51.465
I became a monster.

689
00:42:52.270 --> 00:42:54.068
Uh. completely out of control.

690
00:42:56.307 --> 00:42:57.570
What did you do to her?

691
00:42:58.009 --> 00:42:59.375
Well. we had an argument

692
00:43:00.745 --> 00:43:02.976
in her apartment.
as you guessed.

693
00:43:03.314 --> 00:43:04.407
About what?

694
00:43:05.283 --> 00:43:06.717
The fact that I was married.

695
00:43:08.586 --> 00:43:10.646
- So I was right.
- Yes.

696
00:43:11.722 --> 00:43:15.386
But she told me to leave.

697
00:43:18.262 --> 00:43:21.130
It was me who
was begging to stay.

698
00:43:22.133 --> 00:43:23.133
Why?

699
00:43:25.236 --> 00:43:26.898
Have you ever met someone

700
00:43:27.672 --> 00:43:29.265
who looked at you.

701
00:43:31.142 --> 00:43:34.169
all of you. even
the savage parts.

702
00:43:34.512 --> 00:43:36.344
and they didn't flinch?

703
00:43:38.649 --> 00:43:39.649
No.

704
00:43:39.817 --> 00:43:41.877
I thought she was gonna
be the one to bring me back.

705
00:43:41.953 --> 00:43:45.355
restore me to the man I
was before I went to war.

706
00:43:46.023 --> 00:43:50.222
That night. we
tried to make love...

707
00:43:52.463 --> 00:43:53.463
and...

708
00:43:54.565 --> 00:43:56.033
I found that I couldn't.

709
00:43:56.968 --> 00:43:59.062
For years after Afghanistan.

710
00:43:59.537 --> 00:44:01.768
I had thought the
problem was my wife.

711
00:44:03.274 --> 00:44:05.004
But then. all of a
sudden. it was clear.

712
00:44:06.844 --> 00:44:09.609
The problem had
been me all along.

713
00:44:12.383 --> 00:44:13.715
My fate was sealed.

714
00:44:15.386 --> 00:44:17.548
I would never be the
man I was before the war.

715
00:44:19.357 --> 00:44:23.556
And I was never going to be
enough for Alison or any woman.

716
00:44:24.228 --> 00:44:25.355
So you killed her?

717
00:44:27.365 --> 00:44:29.960
I never felt such rage.

718
00:44:31.602 --> 00:44:34.936
And because Alison was in
front of me. I... I directed it at her.

719
00:44:36.541 --> 00:44:38.476
She said she was leaving.

720
00:44:39.510 --> 00:44:41.035
She ran to the door.

721
00:44:42.113 --> 00:44:44.810
And I didn't want her to go.
so I grabbed her by the arm

722
00:44:45.283 --> 00:44:48.651
to try to bring her back.

723
00:44:49.320 --> 00:44:53.758
and I lost my grip.
and she fell. hard.

724
00:44:55.193 --> 00:44:56.491
against the bookshelf.

725
00:44:58.863 --> 00:45:00.161
Before I could reach her.

726
00:45:00.731 --> 00:45:05.396
this statue. a heavy
statue. it fell on her head.

727
00:45:07.638 --> 00:45:08.998
And she was gone.

728
00:45:12.109 --> 00:45:13.109
So...

729
00:45:13.511 --> 00:45:14.638
it was an accident?

730
00:45:15.146 --> 00:45:16.637
Yes. of course.

731
00:45:17.715 --> 00:45:20.378
I never wanted to
hurt your mother.

732
00:45:34.031 --> 00:45:35.693
I have... I have tried...

733
00:45:37.735 --> 00:45:40.967
to find a way to make
what I did bearable.

734
00:45:41.038 --> 00:45:45.408
I have dedicated the
last 30 years of my life

735
00:45:45.476 --> 00:45:49.470
creating this place: a
safe haven for veterans.

736
00:45:52.416 --> 00:45:55.818
So nobody again

737
00:45:55.886 --> 00:45:58.617
will ever lose
control the way I did.

738
00:45:59.523 --> 00:46:02.823
Hurt someone the
way I hurt your mother.

739
00:46:03.961 --> 00:46:05.361
You didn't just hurt her.

740
00:46:06.464 --> 00:46:07.523
You killed her.

741
00:46:09.333 --> 00:46:11.666
Yes. and I'm sorry. Joanie.

742
